The paper deals with the problem of disambiguating edge crossings in graph and map drawings, which is a common problem in computational geometry and graph theory. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.GR (Graph Theory) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes an algorithm for color assignment, which involves optimization and search techniques, making it relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper gives examples of real-world graphs and maps, which suggests a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
